The main point is:

There is a phenomenon called the "supernormal stimulus." It's like, when a bird lays an egg with blue dots on it, you can put a phony egg in the nest that's bigger, and has brighter colored blue dots on it, and the bird, in her little feathery brain, will say "Aw yeah, that's the shit I was born to take care of," because its shape, size, and coloration press her buttons even harder. And she will ignore her own egg and sit on a painted cue ball, because she's instinctively, genetically, hardwired to respond to the shape and coloration, and the phony one is, for her, more biggerer and more betterer.

And the question the author was thinking about is, what if there's a supernormal stimulus for human sexual attraction? Maybe some specific alien species press our buttons so much harder than potential human partners can that a big segment of humanity just gives up on reproduction in favor of either fucking the aliens or dying in the attempt. Most of the aliens, incidentally, are just doing it for the money. It's not their fault The supernormal stimulus is a narrow focus, and it's a thing one intelligent species feels for a different one. The attraction is not mutual.
